-- India’s Steel Authority Seeks to Import 500,000 Tons Coking Coal
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2012-04-19T05:53:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/india-s-steel-authority-seeks-to-import-500-000-tons-coking-coal.html
Steel Authority of India Ltd. , the
nation’s second-biggest producer of the alloy, is seeking to buy
500,000 metric tons of coking coal from June to November,
according to a tender  notice .  The company wants the first shipment by June or July and
the minimum quantity is one ship of 75,000 tons, the notice
said. Sellers can submit offers by May 14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Archana Chaudhary in  New Delhi  at 
 achaudhary2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
